as to change." The Canadian Obesity Network even suggests a few helpful ways this can happen. Already, it is a lot of self work to overcome weight issues. South African blogger, Nomali Cele, when writing about what she calls her "self acceptance journey" says she has since taken small steps in loving herself and accepting that "whether in size 40 or 46 jeans, I am worthy, lovable, funny, smart and an interesting woman." As Freshlyground aptly put in one of their songs: "Even though I have fat thighs, flabby arms, a pot belly still gives good loving." And might we add, deserves good loving too.